title: Dick Cheney, former US vice president and 'father' of Iraq war, has died
subhed: During President George W. Bush's two terms, Cheney, a foreign policy hawk who was deeply influenced by conservative ideas, embodied the excesses of the war on terror. He died at the age of 84, his family announced on November 4.

title: Trump again taps Musk ally Jared Isaacman to lead NASA

title: PSG forward Dembélé replaced in 1st half of Champions League loss against Bayern Munich

subhed: The Paris Saint-Germain forward had only recently returned following a right hamstring injury sustained while playing for France in September. João Neves pulled one back for PSG, but Bayern Munich wound up beating the title-holders 2-1.

title: 'There's almost no water left': On the front lines of climate change in southern France
